  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Ambient governance is governance that operates through the establishment of conditions rather than the issuance of commands. No law mandates the behavior. No regulation specifies it. No authority commands it. But the behavior spreads because the institutional environment makes it rational — and makes its absence conspicuous.",
  "keywords": "legalism, ambient-governance",
  "name": "ambient governance",
